<TEXT>
china has 670000 beggars and many have turned 
to begging as an easy way to make money an official newspaper said 
today 
the china daily said the nations first conference on the 
homeless which ended in beijing last week concluded that beggars 
pose a hazard to social order and should rouse wide concern 
the daily and other news reports said the number of beggars at 
the end of 1987 was down from 105 million in 1979 but that there 
has been a rise in professional beggars seeking money rather 
than food 
it said only 20 percent of those who beg do so because of 
natural disasters or personal misfortunes most turn to begging for 
the money while others have mental problems or are runaways 
escaping arranged marriages 
