<TEXT>
thor a 6foot2 450pound pet bear 
is enjoying his new country home after being forced out of the 
suburbs says a woman who calls herself his grandma 
thor is very happy he has a pond to splash around in said 
walterine crosby mother of the cinnamonblack bears owners 
we miss him terribly mrs crosby said sunday 
officials in this minneapolis suburb had given charles and 
deborah crosby until sunday to move the bruin from his backyard 
home citing an ordinance prohibiting the keeping of wild animals 
thor was moved friday night to his new digs which the couple 
built on 12 acres outside city limits walterine crosby said 
his new den is made of earthbanked logs and features a 
40by40foot cage and a pond near the crosbys new home the 
nearest neighbors are miles away 
the bloomington city council first tried to banish the bear last 
fall after someone called city hall to report the bear the order 
was delayed because thor was hibernating and nobody wanted to wake 
him up 
charles and deborah crosby said they had planned to move before 
the council banished the bear 
in bloomington thor hibernated in a fencedin concrete den 
built into a hill in the backyard in the summer he wandered 
around the backyard restrained by a loggingchain collar and a 
fence 
the bear has never hurt anyone say the crosbys who got thor 
from a game farm when he was a 5weekold cub his front claws have 
been removed and hes been trained to respond to the command 
dont touch 
