escaped after his arrest for attempting a coup last august ramos 
said renegade soldiers do not have the support or power to 
overthrow the government 
people have been turned off against them he said noting 
that more than 50 people were killed in honasans coup attempt 
we feel that while they have the capability of hitting and 
running their ability to undo the government is now very very 
diminished ramos said 
the military he said also has gone back to basics in its 
training instilling principles that will prevent other soldiers 
from rebelling 
in response to questions about whether he harbors presidential 
