japanese and us naval forces today began a 
weeklong joint antisubmarine drill in the pacific ocean defense 
officials said 
the exercises were held in a 600mile stretch of ocean from 
izuoshima island south of tokyo to japans southwestern main 
island of kyushu said lt cmdr masanobu ohtsuka spokesman for 
the maritime selfdefense force 
