<TEXT>
gay protesters wearing clown masks disrupted a 
tense civil rights commission hearing monday on aids calling the 
session a farce and a waste of money that could have been better 
spent on drug research 
the protesters about 65 members of a new york group called the 
aids coalition to unleash power act up disrupted the meeting for 
nearly an hour with humming heckling and symbolic gestures such as 
turning their backs on the commission and holding up their watches 
to signify that time is running out for aids victims 
the hearing the first of three was part of a controversial 
civil rights commission study of civil rights aspects of public 
health policies and initiatives to control aids including a 
discussion of how aids is transmitted 
the study has drawn fire from lawmakers and others since it was 
proposed last year in a memo that among other things cites state 
antisodomy laws and a court case in the same footnote as lengthy 
biblical condemnations of homosexuality 
do you still want us put to death clarence one protester 
demanded of commission chairman clarence pendleton referring to a 
passage from leviticus recommending just that 
its a waste of time another protester shouted 
spend the money on drug research added a third 
they all filed out wearing their clown masks chanting shame 
shame shame 
this is a total farce said duncan osborne a protester 
these people ought to be taking testimony about discrimination 
against people with aids he said only three victims were 
scheduled to testify in three full days of hearings 
the protest came after a morning session dominated by friction 
among commission members as well as among witnesses on the first 
panel 
those witnesses included a blood bank official a gay rights 
activist a religious hospice operator who said he had moved away 
from the narcissism and contempt of my earlier life as a 
homosexual and a university of minnesota radiologist who claimed 
public health efforts have been thwarted by gay pressure groups 
twentyfive years ago it was southern bullies in jeans that we 
had to fight said dr david pence the radiologist a veteran of 
the civil rights movement now its northern smoothies in ties 
who use middle class conventions to prevent us from using public 
health measures to protect the urban poor 
he has just likened us to the ku klux klan exploded 
jeffrey levi executive director of the national gay and lesbian 
task force he said he could not continue to sit at the same table 
as pence unless the doctor apologized or retracted his statement 
i will not withdraw my basic thesis pence replied the 
gay pressure groups have stopped us from using an effective public 
health policy and theyve done it in the name of civil rights 
the road to selma did not lead to the right to sodomy the 
freedom train has been hijacked 
