on pressure fauci said the evidence is overwhelming 
levi said the gay community had never stood in the way of 
measures to stop aids it is our own lives that we are saving 
he said 
he said gay people support anonymous voluntary testing but they 
fear that if anyone knows they are aids victims or carriers they 
will face discrimination in jobs housing insurance and other 
areas and maybe even prosecution for violating sodomy laws 
he urged the commission to recommend extending protection of the 
handicapped to the private sector and to support laws barring 
discrimination on the basis of sexual orientation 
discussion at the hearing ranged far and wide with pence 
claiming that sexual addicts people who engage in compulsive 
coital behavior outside of marriage need as much rehabilitation 
as drug addicts 
bills barring discrimination against aids victims are pending in 
both house and senate committees the presidential commission on 
aids charged with developing a national aids policy was 
conducting three days of hearings this week on the same days and 
the same subject as the civil rights commission hearings 
