<TEXT>
morocco and algeria announced on monday 
they have restored diplomatic ties and said they want to resolve 
the western sahara dispute that has separated them for 12 years 
a joint statement issued in rabat and algiers said relations 
were being reestablished immediately at the ambassadorial level 
it noted the action followed meetings over the past week in the 
two capitals 
the north african neighbors severed diplomatic ties on march 7 
1976 after algeria recognized the western sahara as the western 
saharan democratic republic morocco had annexed the territory the 
former spanish sahara in 1975 
algeria has sheltered and backed polisario front guerrillas 
fighting morocco for independence of the western sahara 
the joint statement said reestablishment of ties was aimed at 
contributing to the construction of the arab maghreb a unified 
north africa and at endorsing the united nations effort to hold a 
referendum on selfdetermination in the disputed territory 
it said the referendum could offer a just and definitive 
solution 
the announcement precedes a scheduled june 7 arab summit meeting 
in algiers to discuss the palestinian uprising in the 
israelioccupied territories 
it said morocca and algeria have a firm wish to contribute to 
the strengthening of arab ranks around the sacred cause of the 
palestinian people by reinforcing their heroic uprising in the 
occupied territories 
fighting between the polisario guerrillas and moroccan soldiers 
has at times brought morocco and algeria to the brink of war 
</TEXT>
