become our new ambassador for the republic of letters he added 
billington also cited nemerov 68 for his work as an 
outstanding critic essayist fiction writer and teacher 
nemerov currently a distinguished professor at washington 
university i8n st louis will succeed richard wilbur and robert 
penn warren in holding the endowed chair created by congress in 
1936 for the position of consultant in poetry to the library 
in that capacity nemerov will give a public poetry reading and 
lecture advise the library on its literary programs and recommend 
new poets to be included in the librarys archive of recorded 
poetry and literature 
nemerov previously served as a consultant in poetry to the 
library in 1963 
nemerov won both the pulitzer prize and national book award in 
poetry in 1978 among his collections of poetry are image and the 
