<TEXT>
when jimmy carter as president needed to get away for a while 
before he went to camp david with israeli prime minister menachem 
begin and egyptian president anwar sadat his thoughts turned to 
fly fishing 
when i was president rosalynn and i fly fished out west he 
says on the precamp david trip i took along with me the 
briefing books that i would be using to prepare myself for the 
mideast negotiations so it was a combination of delightful 
surroundings good companionsand also just clearing my mind when 
i was ready to embark on one of the major challenges of my 
presidency 
he now fly fishes throughout the world but loves to come home 
to north georgia to the little log cabin he furnished with his 
handmade wooden furniture 
the cabin is within 20 feet of turnip town creek which has a 
fairly good native population of rainbow trout its the perfect 
environment for writing in placid beautiful surroundings in 
almost total isolation when rosalynn and i are there which is 
never enough it makes for good thoughts and productive days 
the former president has written a new book an outdoor 
journal reflections and adventures recalling favorite fishing 
experiences writing it he said was a labor of love 
jack hemingway i bet i was the only american in world war ii 
who parachuted into occupied france with a fly rod i used it 
too 
the son of legendary fisherman and writer ernest hemingway now 
lives in ketchum idaho between angling excursions to distant 
parts of the globe but some of his most vivid memories are of his 
happy days on clear rivers with his father 
when i was 6 before id ever picked up a fly rod i spent one 
whole summer watching him fish the clarks fork river of the 
yellowstone hemingway says finally at the very end when id 
spent the whole summer building up the need to fish my father 
taught me how to cast 
author of misadventures of a fly fisherman jack hemingway 
