both my parents were fishermen my mother once held a blue 
marlin record and since i was an only child i spent a lot of time 
doing male sort of things with them i grew up before the womens 
lib thing so fishing taught me how to do things on my own taught 
me i could go off alone without needing any help in those days 
there werent that many things which could teach women to be 
independent but fly fishing was one of them 
mrs morgens and her husband ned live in south norwalk conn 
