<TEXT>
here are some facts and figures on romania 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the land in southeastern europe romania is about the size of 
oregon and shares borders with hungary yugoslavia the soviet 
union and bulgaria the danube forms most of its border with 
bulgaria before it turns northeast and empties into the black sea 
much of the land is rich for farming wheat corn sugar beets 
potatoes and wine grapes northern romania is dominated by the 
carpathian mountains and the transylvanian alps 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the people the population of nearly 23 million includes about 
2 million ethnic hungarians and about 220000 ethnic germans 
romanian is the main language but hungarian serbian german and 
turkish also are spoken eighty percent of the population is 
romanian orthodox christian and 10 percent are roman catholics 
about 22000 jews live in romania 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the economy industry accounts for around 60 percent of the 
gross national product the economy is exportoriented to earn hard 
western currencies but this has meant shortages at home of basic 
goods romania exports machinery metals lumber refined fuels 
textiles and farm products its natural resources include oil 
natural gas and coal romanians are living through a period of 
harsh austerity as the government seeks to pay off a foreign debt 
that reached 11 billion in 1981 but now is down to 45 billion 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
history after five centuries of ottoman rule romania gained 
its independence in 1877 a monarchy before world war ii the 
country was reorganized along fascist progerman lines from 1940 
until aug 23 1944 when romania switched to the allied side with 
the support of soviet troops a communistdominated government bloc 
won elections in 1946 and in 1955 romania joined the east blocs 
warsaw pact president nicolae ceausescu who came to power in 
1965 is noted for his independent foreign policy but is under 
increasing fire for his domestic policy including suppression of 
dissent and alleged discrimination against the hungarian minority 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

