<TEXT>
an unusual recruiting effort proved that 
a job seeker can make progress while stuck in a traffic jam 
johnson memorial hospital in stafford earlier this year leased a 
billboard overlooking a busy section of interstate 91 in hartford 
for two months advertising openings on its nursing staff 
the hospital was feeling the impact of the nationwide nursing 
shortage and had been forced to turn patients away or refer them 
to other hospitals officials said 
the billboard read attention healthcare professionals if 
you worked at johnson memorial hospital you would be home by now 
stephen e torla vice president of human resources at johnson 
memorial said the billboard resulted in five vacancies being 
filled and inquiries about employment were received from as far 
away as missouri and new jersey 
the billboard was good as far as employee moral good as a 
recruitment tool and good exposure torla said adding that 
there are still some nursing vacancies at the hospital 
elizabeth a nelson vice president of financing at johnson 
memorial said the hospital is considering renewing the billboards 
lease to attract other hardtofind employees such as laboratory 
technicians respiratory therapists and operating room technicians 
