the pilot program merges the universitys strong german language 
curriculum with its engineering school according to a spokesman 
the standard fouryear engineering program is combined with 
specially designed german courses in the first three years 
students take a separate german program honing technical language 
skills 
this is followed by a oneyear internship in a germanspeaking 
country with the fifth year devoted to advanced german courses as 
well as interdisciplinary engineering courses taught all in german 
