<TEXT>
eastern airlines and continental airlines on 
monday announced new cutrate fares for children and senior 
citizens for the summer and at least one other major airline 
quickly followed suit 
the two airlines also said they were easing some restrictions 
now attached to regular maxsaver deepdiscount fares 
the new junior and senior maxsavers which range from 29 to 99 
one way are about 30 percent lower than current maxsaver fares 
they are available for travel between june 1 and sept 11 for 
children under 18 and seniors over 65 
these new fares make summer travel more affordable for the 
entire family continental president martin shugrue told a 
televised news conference originating in new york and los angeles 
grandparents can share in a summer excursion at a price that is 
practical even on a fixed income 
continental launched a media blitz to publicize the new fares 
including a series of television commercials featuring nonagenarian 
comedian george burns 
i dont think this is a panicked response to lower passenger 
demand said anthony hatch an airline analyst for argus research 
corp he said the new fares mainly designed to garner favorable 
publicity for the beleaguered carriers are not likely to have a 
significant impact on their profit 
eastern and continental both subsidiaries of giant texas air 
corp are the targets of new highly publicized federal 
investigations into their finances and the safety of their fleets 
the two airlines said they were cutting fares for children and 
seniors because they have found those segments of the flying public 
to be very sensitive to price changes airlines normally raise 
fares at this time of the year since it is the start of the peak 
travel season 
some observers suggested privately however that eastern and 
continental may have introduced the cheap fares to fill seats made 
vacant by slack summer bookings partly due to negative publicity 
from the new federal inspections 
united airlines the nations largest carrier said monday it 
will match the special fares in the markets where it competes with 
continental 
continental is a major competitor of ours said united 
spokesman joe hopkins noting that both airlines have major hubs at 
denver 
spokesmen for northwest airlines american airlines and delta 
air lines said officials of those carriers were studying the new 
fares and considering matching them 
eastern and continental also said they were loosening some 
restrictions on regular maxsaver fares for a price in some cases 
the new rules allow travelers to change the flight on the return 
portion of their maxsaver ticket when the change is made before the 
scheduled departure time of the original return flight and at 
least two days before the departure of the new flight a 75 
service charge must be paid to make the changes 
minimumstay requirements were eased by allowing fliers to 
return after 4 pm on saturday rather than the current obligation 
to stay past midnight that day 
maxsavers are good for travel between noon on mondays and noon 
on thursdays they must be purchased in advance for a round trip 
and are nonrefundable 
the new fares for children and senior citizens carry the same 
restrictions as the regular liberalized maxsavers and children 
flying on junior maxsavers must be accompanied by an adult who can 
use any fare 
in addition to the junior and senior maxsavers eastern is 
offering a summer roundtrip fare of 79 to 99 for children to fly 
to 14 florida cities 
